---
By: Arthur S. Hardy
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 224
    Verse: 12
Tags:
  - Happiness
---
Set happiness before you as an end, no matter in what guise of wealth, or
fame, or oblivion even, and you will not attain it. But renounce it and
seek the pleasure of God, and that instant is the birth of your own.
